Let's first expand the right side of the equation:

\begin{align*}
\left( x^2-50x-10\right)\left( x^2+25x+5\right) &= x^4 + 25x^3 + 5x^2 - 50x^3 - 1250x^2 - 250x - 10x^2 - 250x - 50 \\
&= x^4 - 25x^3 - 1255x^2 - 500x - 50.
\end{align*}

Now we set this equal to $\frac{1}{2}\left( 3x^2-1\right)$:

\begin{align*}
x^4 - 25x^3 - 1255x^2 - 500x - 50 &= \frac{1}{2}\left( 3x^2-1\right) \\
x^4 - 25x^3 - 1255x^2 - 500x - 50 &= \frac{3}{2}x^2 - \frac{1}{2} \\
x^4 - 25x^3 - 1258.5x^2 - 500x - 50 &= 0.
\end{align*}

Now, this is a quartic equation, so we must find the roots using a numerical method. By graphing the equation or using a calculator, we find the positive real root to be approximately $x \approx 46.05$. Thus, the solution is $\boxed{46.05}$.
